summary:
Hi there! My name is Paris and I'm a zoology student with a particular interest in Animal Genetics, currently studying penguin behaviour at Antwerp Zoo. In addition to my scientific pursuits, I have a passion for writing and translation, which has been greatly influenced by my bilingual upbringing in Dutch and English. I believe that effective communication is key to connecting with others and fostering understanding, and I enjoy using my skills to bridge linguistic and cultural divides.

In addition to my academic and language-based interests, I also have a creative side and have founded my own fashion brand. I draw inspiration from the beauty and diversity of the natural world and believe that fashion can be a powerful way to celebrate and express our unique identities.

I'm always seeking new opportunities to learn, grow, and make a positive impact, and I welcome the chance to connect with others who share my interests and values. If you'd like to chat more about my background and experiences, please don't hesitate to reach out on LinkedIn. Looking forward to connecting!
